16. Let the function $f(x)=p x-\frac{p}{x}-2 \ln x$.
(1) If $f(x)$ is a monotonically increasing function in its domain, find the range of the real number $p$;
(2) Let $g(x)=\frac{2 e}{x}$, and $p>0$, if there exists at least one point $x_{0}$ in $[1, e]$ such that $f\left(x_{0}\right)>g\left(x_{0}\right)$, find the range of the real number $p$;
(3) Prove that for any positive integer $n$, $\sum_{k=1}^{n} \ln ^{2}\left(1+\frac{2}{k}\right)<3$ holds.

15 (20 points) Given the function $f(x)=\mathrm{e}^{x}-x$, (where $\mathrm{e}$ is an irrational number, $\mathrm{e}=$ 2. $71828 \cdots$)
(1) If the function $g(x)=f(x)-a x^{2}-1$ has a derivative $g^{\prime}(x)$ that is an increasing function on $[0,+\infty)$, try to find the maximum value of the real number $a$;
(2) Prove that: $f\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)+f\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)+\cdots+f\left(\frac{1}{n}\right)>n\left[1+\frac{1}{4(n+2)}\right]$, where $n \in \mathbf{N}^{*}$.

16 Let the function $f(x)=x(1+x)^{2}, x \in(-\infty, 0]$.
(1) Find the extremum points of $f(x)$;
(2) For any $a<0$, let $F(a)$ denote the point where $f(x)$ attains its minimum value on $[a, 0]$, find the minimum value of $k=$ $\frac{F(a)}{a}$.

14. Given $a>0, f(x)=\ln (2 x+1)+2 a x-4 a e^{x}+4$.
(1) When $a=1$, find the maximum value of $f(x)$;
(2) Determine the number of zeros of the function $f(x)$, and explain the reason.
